page.title: 14EDUCATION IN KEYINGHAm
page.content: Keyingham has an infants and junior school, children from Ottingham, Halsham, Sunk Island and all the immediate surrounding area attend these schools. The infants schools takes children aged 5 to 7, the junior school takes children aged 7 to 12, the children then transfer to a secondary school which is at Withernsea some 13 miles away. Free transport is provided for children and all schools provide a meals service, allowing children to have a cooked lunch at midday, the minimum cost is 60 pence.
